Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream

Class PacketUtils

java.lang.Object
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream.PacketUtils
public class PacketUtils extends Object
Contains a number of static Packet objects of commonly used packets and several static methods for creating useful packet lists.

    • WRITE_PACKETS

      public static PacketList WRITE_PACKETS(RegisterType register, List<Integer> data) throws BitstreamException
      Create the necessary packets for writing data. If the data can fit in a single type 1 packet (less than Packet.MAX_TYPE_ONE_SIZE), a single type one write packet will be created. If it is too large to fit in a type 1 packet but small enough for a type 2 packet, a zero word type 1 packet followed by a type 2 packet will be created. If there are too many words for a type 2 packet, an exception will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      data - The data to write into the packets.
      Returns:
      The resulting packet list.
      Throws:
      BitstreamException
